      "content": "That makes sense. Some people might argue that these regulations are actually necessary to prevent harm, like protecting kids or stopping misinformation, and that this isn't \"censorship\" but just \"safety.\" Do you think those arguments have any real intellectual weight, or are they just excuses to justify government control?",
